<p>GigaCheck is designed to identify AI-generated content at two granularit=
ies:</p>




















<table><thead><tr><th>Task</th><th>Output</th><th>Use Case</th></tr></thead=
><tbody><tr><td>Classification</td><td>Document-level label (<code class=3D=
"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal lead=
ing-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">human</code>, <=
code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs fon=
t-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">ai=
</code>, or <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem=
] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#4=
84848]/30">mixed</code>)</td><td>Filtering, binary detection</td></tr><tr><=
td>Detection</td><td>Character interval spans marking AI-generated regions<=
/td><td>Fine-grained localization, mixed-authorship analysis</td></tr></tbo=
dy></table>
<p>Both tasks share a common Mistral-7B-v0.3 foundation but employ task-spe=
cific heads: LoRA-adapted classification head for document labels, and DETR=
-based architecture for interval prediction.</p>
